WEBVTT

00:02.473 --> 00:04.535
ALL RIGHT, LET´S TRY
THE PROBLEM AGAIN.

00:04.535 --> 00:06.337
BUT I DON´T GET IT!

00:06.337 --> 00:08.109
THEY DON´T EVEN
LOOK LIKE NUMBERS.

00:08.109 --> 00:10.711
THIS IS ALL MIXED UP!
I HATE DYSLEXIA!

00:10.711 --> 00:15.646
HONEY, WHEN YOU MIX UP NUMBERS,
IT´S CALLED "DYSCALCULIA."

00:17.688 --> 00:20.321
MOM, MY EYES ARE TIRED.

00:20.321 --> 00:22.493
OKAY, LET ME HELP,
OKAY?

00:22.493 --> 00:24.225
I WENT THROUGH
THE SAME THING.

00:24.225 --> 00:26.227
IT´S NOT THAT HARD.

00:28.259 --> 00:33.334
OKAY, MAX, 1-5 IS 15...

00:33.334 --> 00:39.310
AND .00 IS
THE HUNDREDTHS.

00:39.310 --> 00:41.512
HELLO?

00:44.245 --> 00:47.218
AND PERCENTS, RIGHT?

00:47.218 --> 00:50.651
PERCENTS MEAN --
MEANS THE HUNDREDTHS.

00:59.390 --> 01:00.791
SO...

01:02.693 --> 01:08.539
SO .15 IS 15 PER--

01:08.539 --> 01:11.542
IS 15 PERCENT OF --

01:11.542 --> 01:13.674
MY EYES ARE TIRED!

01:16.147 --> 01:17.678
SEE?

01:17.678 --> 01:21.412
MAX, YOUR EYES WERE TIRED
WHEN WE STARTED.

01:21.412 --> 01:24.155
ALL RIGHT, LET´S JUST
TAKE A BREAK, HUH?

01:26.657 --> 01:29.490
RELAX, OKAY?
MATH TAKES TIME.

01:29.490 --> 01:32.693
GEORGE, THE STATE PROFICIENCY
TEST IS ONLY THREE WEEKS AWAY.

01:32.693 --> 01:34.325
HE DOESN´T HAVE TIME.

01:34.325 --> 01:36.297
WELL, THEN,
WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO?

01:36.297 --> 01:38.829
BECAUSE I DON´T UNDERSTAND IT,
YOU CAN´T EXPLAIN IT.

01:42.133 --> 01:45.105
IT´S LIKE THE FIRST NIGHT
OF OUR HONEYMOON.

01:50.311 --> 01:52.183
IT´S NOT JUST MATH.

01:52.183 --> 01:54.845
IT´S ALL THE SUBJECTS.
HE´S NOT GETTING IT.

01:54.845 --> 01:57.588
SO WHAT HAPPENS IF HE
FAILS THE PROFICIENCY TEST?

01:57.588 --> 01:59.550
HE GETS HELD BACK.

01:59.550 --> 02:02.723
OH, YOU PEOPLE
AND YOUR EDUCATION.

02:02.723 --> 02:06.197
"EVERYBODY´S
GOT TO GO TO COLLEGE."

02:06.197 --> 02:09.730
PIZZAS DON´T
DELIVER THEMSELVES.

02:14.665 --> 02:16.667
OKAY.

02:18.439 --> 02:21.772
WE´RE GONNA DO SOMETHING FOR MAX
THAT MY MOTHER NEVER DID FOR ME.

02:21.772 --> 02:24.675
YOU´RE GONNA
BREAST-FEED HIM?

02:24.675 --> 02:27.918
WE´RE GONNA GO OUTSIDE THE
FAMILY AND GET SOMEBODY TO HELP.

02:27.918 --> 02:29.680
WE´RE GONNA GET HIM
A TUTOR.

02:29.680 --> 02:32.853
YOU DON´T NEED
A TUTOR!

02:32.853 --> 02:36.357
YOU KNOW,
HAVING A DUMB KID...

02:39.190 --> 02:41.662
NOTHING TO BE ASHAMED OF --
I WASN´T.

02:45.696 --> 02:48.839
[ INTRO TO WAR´S "LOW RIDER"
PLAYS ]

02:56.907 --> 03:01.812
♫ ALL MY FRIENDS
KNOW THE LOW RIDER ♫

03:38.489 --> 03:40.351
IS THAT THE NEW TUTOR?

03:40.351 --> 03:42.693
YEP. NUMBER FIVE.

03:42.693 --> 03:44.255
LOOKS LIKE WE FINALLY
GOT A GOOD ONE.

03:46.957 --> 03:49.630
HE´S PAYING ATTENTION.
MMM.

03:50.701 --> 03:54.305
OKAY, SWEETIE,
LET´S TRY IT THIS WAY.

03:54.305 --> 03:55.866
"X" IS MY SECRET,

03:55.866 --> 03:58.909
AND YOU WANT TO FIGURE
MY SECRET OUT.

03:58.909 --> 04:00.841
SO I´M GONNA
GIVE YOU A CLUE.

04:00.841 --> 04:04.244
2 TIMES "X" EQUALS...

04:05.746 --> 04:08.018
OH, I JUST GOT A CHILL.

04:11.622 --> 04:14.325
MAX,
YOU´RE NOT CONCENTRATING.

04:14.325 --> 04:18.789
YOU KNOW, WHEN I MAKE
MY PARENTS MAD, THEY TICKLE ME.

04:21.292 --> 04:22.763
MAX...

04:22.763 --> 04:24.935
MAX...
[ CHUCKLES ]

04:27.698 --> 04:28.469
WOW.

04:28.469 --> 04:30.270
YOU KNOW,

04:30.270 --> 04:33.273
I READ THAT WOMEN THAT ARE THAT
BEAUTIFUL DON´T HAVE BOYFRIENDS

04:33.273 --> 04:36.507
´CAUSE GUYS ARE TOO INTIMATED
TO COME UP AND TALK TO THEM.

04:36.507 --> 04:37.778
HUH.

04:37.778 --> 04:39.450
WELL, ADD ME
TO THE LIST, MAN!

04:44.385 --> 04:48.288
HE´S ONLY PAYING ATTENTION
BECAUSE SHE´S SO PRETTY.

04:48.288 --> 04:50.921
WELL, SOMETIMES YOU NEED
AN ATTRACTIVE WOMAN

04:50.921 --> 04:52.423
TO GET A MAN´S ATTENTION.

04:52.423 --> 04:53.924
YOU KNOW
WHAT I´M TALKING ABOUT --

04:53.924 --> 04:55.426
THAT SHORT SKIRT YOU WEAR

04:55.426 --> 04:58.599
WHEN YOU WANT ME TO SEE
A JUDE LAW MOVIE.

04:58.599 --> 05:01.832
OKAY, I´LL EXPLAIN
WHY WE CAN´T BE TOGETHER

05:01.832 --> 05:03.804
IN MATHEMATICAL TERMS.

05:03.804 --> 05:06.537
YOU´RE 11, AND I´M 22.

05:06.537 --> 05:09.309
SO WHEN YOU´RE 18,
I´LL BE...

05:09.309 --> 05:12.343
IT DOESN´T MATTER.
I´LL BE 18.

05:14.645 --> 05:17.317
I THINK WE´RE DONE
WITH THIS.

05:20.651 --> 05:22.052
HI.

05:22.052 --> 05:24.825
I´M SORRY, I DON´T THINK
I´M GETTING THROUGH TO MAX.

05:24.825 --> 05:27.658
I SEEM TO HAVE A TOUGH TIME
WITH THE BOYS...

05:27.658 --> 05:30.531
AND THIS ONE GIRL
WHO LOOKS LIKE CLAY AIKEN

05:30.531 --> 05:33.564
WHO JUST STARES AT ME
AND BITES HER LIP.

05:34.805 --> 05:37.508
WELL, WE APPRECIATE
YOUR EFFORT, ASHLEY.

05:37.508 --> 05:38.639
HOW MUCH DO WE OWE YOU?

05:38.639 --> 05:40.571
WELL, IT´S $30
FOR THE HOUR

05:40.571 --> 05:45.446
AND, LET´S JUST SAY,
$2 FOR MY SCRUNCHIE.

05:48.018 --> 05:49.680
OH...

05:51.722 --> 05:52.983
THANKS.

05:52.983 --> 05:54.685
BYE.
BYE.

05:56.627 --> 05:58.689
MAX, WHAT HAPPENED?

05:58.689 --> 06:00.461
I´LL TELL YOU
WHAT HAPPENED.

06:00.461 --> 06:01.832
ANOTHER LOUSY TUTOR!

06:01.832 --> 06:05.396
MAX, FINISH YOUR MATH
IN THE BACKYARD.

06:05.396 --> 06:07.898
AH, YOU CAN PLAY
WITH THE SCRUNCHIE

06:07.898 --> 06:10.601
WHEN YOU´RE DONE
WITH YOUR HOMEWORK.

06:10.601 --> 06:12.973
I WANT HER SMELL,
NOT YOURS.

06:15.446 --> 06:16.847
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

06:16.847 --> 06:18.549
I´M GONNA FIND
ANOTHER TUTOR.

06:18.549 --> 06:22.012
GEORGE, THIS ISN´T WORKING,
AND IT´S NOT THE TUTORS.

06:22.012 --> 06:23.914
THEY´VE HELPED
OTHER DYSLEXIC KIDS.

06:23.914 --> 06:24.715
IT´S MAX.

06:24.715 --> 06:26.417
NO, IT´S NOT.

06:26.417 --> 06:29.990
LOOK, MAYBE HE´S NOT MATURE
ENOUGH TO TAKE THIS SERIOUSLY.

06:29.990 --> 06:31.992
I THINK IT WOULD BE
GOOD FOR HIM

06:31.992 --> 06:34.765
TO SPEND ANOTHER YEAR
IN THE FIFTH GRADE TO GROW UP.

06:34.765 --> 06:36.096
NO WAY!

06:36.096 --> 06:37.568
LOOK, THIS ISN´T ABOUT
MATURITY, ANGIE.

06:37.568 --> 06:39.430
YOU NEVER HAD
A LEARNING DISABILITY.

06:39.430 --> 06:41.131
THERE´S GOT TO BE SOMEBODY
OUT THERE WHO CAN HELP HIM.

06:41.131 --> 06:43.904
THE TEST
IS TWO WEEKS AWAY.

06:43.904 --> 06:46.577
HE´S NOT GONNA GET ALGEBRA
IN TWO WEEKS.

06:46.577 --> 06:48.108
ANGIE...

06:48.108 --> 06:50.010
[ Squealing voice ]
I GOT THIS!

06:50.010 --> 06:52.783
I WILL FIND A BETTER TUTOR --
SOMEBODY OLD SCHOOL WITH THE --

06:52.783 --> 06:55.185
♫ WHOOP-DI-WHOOP ♫

06:55.185 --> 06:57.888
"OLD TEACHER WILLING
TO DISCIPLINE YOUNG STUDENT."

06:57.888 --> 07:00.120
HUH? HOW ABOUT THAT?
OH.

07:02.923 --> 07:04.925
OHH.

07:04.925 --> 07:06.497
HEY, GUYS.

07:07.928 --> 07:09.099
JASON WALKED ME HOME.

07:09.099 --> 07:10.631
IS IT OKAY
IF HE STAYS FOR DINNER?

07:10.631 --> 07:12.432
SURE, BUT I THOUGHT
YOU WERE MAD AT HIM

07:12.432 --> 07:14.104
FOR NOT SPENDING
ENOUGH TIME WITH YOU.

07:14.104 --> 07:19.470
YEAH, BUT I MADE HIM PROMISE NOT
TO TAKE ON ANY MORE ACTIVITIES.

07:19.470 --> 07:20.871
I´M HIS PRIORITY.

07:20.871 --> 07:22.442
NOW, DID HE SAY THAT,

07:22.442 --> 07:24.975
OR DID YOU SAY THAT,
AND HE JUST SAID,

07:24.975 --> 07:27.548
"UH-HUH...

07:27.548 --> 07:29.620
"UH-HUH...

07:29.620 --> 07:30.951
UH-HUH"?

07:30.951 --> 07:32.823
SO YOU HAVING TROUBLE
WITH THIS, BUDDY?

07:32.823 --> 07:34.485
YEAH.

07:34.485 --> 07:37.558
YEAH, MY BROTHER HAD TROUBLE
WITH ALGEBRA, TOO.

07:37.558 --> 07:41.762
SO WE CAME UP
WITH A LITTLE RHYME.

07:41.762 --> 07:43.594
"ALGEBRA´S CRAP.

07:43.594 --> 07:44.995
"IT´S A WASTE OF GAS.

07:44.995 --> 07:46.767
"SEE YOUR TEACHER SITTIN´
ON HER BIG FAT...

07:46.767 --> 07:49.900
"ASK ME HOW TO DO IT,
AND I´LL TELL YOU, BROTHER.

07:49.900 --> 07:53.103
"JUST DO TO ONE SIDE
WHAT YOU DO TO THE OTHER.

07:53.103 --> 07:55.646
"TAKE THE BOTTOM NUMBER.
YOU MULTIPLY.

07:55.646 --> 07:59.810
YOU SEE WHAT I´M DOIN´?
AND I´M NOT HIGH."

07:59.810 --> 08:03.684
DO TO ONE SIDE
WHAT YOU DO TO THE OTHER.

08:03.684 --> 08:07.087
"X" EQUALS 8?

08:07.087 --> 08:08.659
THAT´S IT.

08:08.659 --> 08:11.962
I GOT ONE!
I GOT ONE RIGHT!

08:11.962 --> 08:15.666
MOM, DAD,
I SOLVED A PROBLEM.

08:15.666 --> 08:17.197
JASON SHOWED ME
HOW TO DO IT.

08:17.197 --> 08:18.799
REALLY?

08:18.799 --> 08:20.000
CAN YOU TUTOR HIM?

08:20.000 --> 08:21.071
DAD!

08:21.071 --> 08:23.003
FIFTEEN BUCKS AN HOUR.

08:23.003 --> 08:25.505
BUT YOU GUYS
PAID ASHLEY $30.

08:26.637 --> 08:30.581
QUIET! YOU DON´T KNOW MATH!
GET OVER HERE.

08:30.581 --> 08:33.013
I GUESS I CAN
FIND THE TIME.

08:33.013 --> 08:34.745
NO!

08:34.745 --> 08:36.747
JASON, YOU SAID YOU WOULDN´T
TAKE ON ANY MORE ACTIVITIES.

08:36.747 --> 08:38.589
I CAN DO IT
IN A HALF-HOUR A DAY,

08:38.589 --> 08:39.920
AND WE´LL SEE
EACH OTHER MORE.

08:39.920 --> 08:42.152
COME ON, YOUR LITTLE BROTHER
NEEDS HELP IN MATH.

08:42.152 --> 08:44.054
FINE.

08:44.054 --> 08:46.657
BUT MAX WON´T NEED TO KNOW MATH
FOR HIS JOB, ANYWAY.

08:46.657 --> 08:47.998
WHEN SOMEONE
ORDERS A HAMBURGER,

08:47.998 --> 08:49.830
HE´LL JUST PRESS
THE HAMBURGER PICTURE!

08:52.763 --> 08:54.905
DID YOU HEAR THAT,
BUDDY?

08:54.905 --> 08:59.009
SHE PUT YOU RIGHT UP FRONT,
AT THE REGISTER!

09:00.741 --> 09:03.273
SOMEBODY BELIEVES IN YOU,
MI HIJO.

09:07.878 --> 09:09.279
WHAT´S THE MATTER,
MAX?

09:09.279 --> 09:11.622
WE GOT THE GRADES BACK
ON OUR PRACTICE TESTS,

09:11.622 --> 09:13.053
AND I NEED THEM SIGNED.

09:13.053 --> 09:16.857
OH, HONEY,
WE KNOW YOU TRIED HARD,

09:16.857 --> 09:18.859
AND THAT´S THE MOST
IMPORTANT THING.

09:18.859 --> 09:21.291
SAVE THAT FOR THE LOSERS
WHO SUCK IN EVERY SUBJECT.

09:21.291 --> 09:23.634
I GOT A "B" IN MATH!

09:29.169 --> 09:31.241
"D" MINUS.

09:31.241 --> 09:32.743
"D" MINUS.

09:32.743 --> 09:35.646
"D" MINUS.

09:35.646 --> 09:37.908
"B"!

09:37.908 --> 09:40.881
[ GASPS ]
THIS IS AMAZING!

09:40.881 --> 09:42.582
George: YES!

09:42.582 --> 09:45.686
NOW I KNOW WHAT
A KOREAN FATHER FEELS LIKE!

09:48.358 --> 09:50.761
WAY TO GO, MAX.

09:50.761 --> 09:52.963
LOOK, JASON,
YOU HELPED MAX IN MATH,

09:52.963 --> 09:55.595
BUT HE´S SUCKIN´
IN ALL HIS OTHER SUBJECTS.

09:55.595 --> 09:58.368
IF YOU COULD TUTOR HIM
IN ALL THOSE OTHER SUBJECTS,

09:58.368 --> 10:01.872
HE MIGHT MAKE IT
TO THE SIXTH GRADE.

10:01.872 --> 10:04.074
THEN, ONE DAY WHEN YOU´RE
RUNNING FOR PRESIDENT,

10:04.074 --> 10:06.677
YOU CAN SAY THAT YOU HELPED
A LITTLE BROWN BOY.

10:08.078 --> 10:09.780
DAD, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

10:09.780 --> 10:11.942
CARMEN,
LET HIM ANSWER.

10:13.313 --> 10:15.746
JASON,
HELP THE LITTLE BROWN BOY.

10:19.219 --> 10:21.391
ALL RIGHT, I´LL HELP.
OH, MY GOD!

10:23.353 --> 10:25.255
I BETTER GO
TALK TO HER.

10:25.255 --> 10:28.198
OH, HEY,
JUST A LITTLE ADVICE.

10:28.198 --> 10:31.401
BEFORE SHE CRIES,
YOU CRY.

10:33.233 --> 10:35.766
THEN SAY, "I´M SORRY.

10:35.766 --> 10:38.338
I DON´T DESERVE
TO TALK TO YOU RIGHT NOW."

10:38.338 --> 10:41.872
THEN RUN AND WIPE YOUR EYES
LIKE THAT.

10:45.345 --> 10:46.717
CARMEN...

10:46.717 --> 10:48.118
HOW CAN YOU DO
MORE TUTORING?

10:48.118 --> 10:49.920
YOU´VE ALREADY GOT
LIKE A MILLION ACTIVITIES.

10:49.920 --> 10:51.882
BASKETBALL, DEBATE,
STUDENT COUNCIL...

10:51.882 --> 10:53.854
AND EVERYTHING
IS MORE IMPORTANT THAN ME.

10:53.854 --> 10:55.185
IT´S NOT MORE IMPORTANT
THAN YOU.

10:55.185 --> 10:56.857
I JUST NEED ALL THAT STUFF
FOR MY TRANSCRIPT.

10:56.857 --> 10:59.059
OH, OKAY, WELL,
I´M SORRY OUR RELATIONSHIP

10:59.059 --> 11:00.991
CAN´T GET YOU
TO A BETTER COLLEGE.

11:00.991 --> 11:02.893
MAYBE YOU DON´T HAVE TIME
FOR A GIRLFRIEND.

11:02.893 --> 11:05.395
YEAH, MAYBE I DON´T.
[ GASPS ]

11:06.666 --> 11:08.769
LOOK AT THEM
FIGHTING OUT THERE.

11:08.769 --> 11:10.070
THIS IS YOUR FAULT.

11:10.070 --> 11:13.373
ONCE HE CRIES AND RUNS,
IT WILL BE FINE.

11:15.145 --> 11:17.447
THAT DOESN´T EVEN WORK
WHEN YOU DO IT.

11:20.080 --> 11:23.453
[ SNIFFS ] I KNOW.

11:23.453 --> 11:25.285
I DON´T DESERVE TO TALK
TO YOU RIGHT NOW.

11:25.285 --> 11:26.386
I´M GONNA GO PLAY GOLF.

11:26.386 --> 11:28.889
I DON´T THINK SO.

11:29.960 --> 11:31.822
EVERYTHING OKAY, HONEY?
NO!

11:31.822 --> 11:34.464
NO -- THANKS TO YOU,
JASON AND I JUST BROKE UP.

11:34.464 --> 11:36.797
I DON´T EVER WANT TO SEE HIM
IN THIS HOUSE AGAIN.

11:38.368 --> 11:40.700
OKAY,
I´LL TAKE CARE OF THIS.

11:40.700 --> 11:44.805
OH, JASON, HOLD UP MAN.
YOU CAN´T DO THIS.

11:44.805 --> 11:46.236
LOOK, MR. LOPEZ,

11:46.236 --> 11:48.238
I´M SORRY IT DIDN´T WORK OUT
BETWEEN ME AND CARMEN.

11:48.238 --> 11:49.740
OKAY, SO AM I.

11:49.740 --> 11:51.441
OKAY, CARMEN IS ONE
OF THE SWEETEST,

11:51.441 --> 11:53.013
MOST WONDERFUL GIRLS
IN THE WORLD,

11:53.013 --> 11:54.945
AND SHE DOESN´T DESERVE
ANY OF THIS.

11:56.446 --> 11:59.790
BUT I´M TALKIN´ ABOUT MAX.

12:03.393 --> 12:06.496
I DON´T WANT HIM TO FAIL, BUT
CARMEN´S NOT GONNA WANT ME HERE.

12:06.496 --> 12:08.759
LOOK, I´LL GET MY DAUGHTER
THROUGH THIS, OKAY?

12:08.759 --> 12:11.031
YOU JUST KEEP
HELPING MY BOY.

12:11.031 --> 12:13.233
I GUESS,
BUT IT´S GONNA BE AWKWARD.

12:13.233 --> 12:15.465
NOT AS AWKWARD AS DROPPING OFF
A 21-YEAR-OLD KID

12:15.465 --> 12:17.407
AT THE FIFTH GRADE!

12:18.468 --> 12:20.070
"GOOD LUCK, MAX.

12:20.070 --> 12:22.843
YOUR MOM PACKED YOU SOME PUDDING
AND A 40-OUNCE."

12:27.147 --> 12:29.119
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

12:31.021 --> 12:32.823
HOW YOU DOING,
SWEETHEART?

12:32.823 --> 12:34.855
I FEEL LIKE JASON
RIPPED OUT MY HEART

12:34.855 --> 12:37.127
AND STOMPED ON IT
RIGHT IN FRONT OF ME.

12:37.127 --> 12:38.889
I´M SORRY, HONEY.

12:38.889 --> 12:41.761
YOU KNOW WHAT YOU COULD DO
TO GET YOUR MIND OFF JASON?

12:41.761 --> 12:43.794
VOLUNTEER.

12:46.766 --> 12:49.169
JOIN SOME CLUBS, CARMEN.

12:49.169 --> 12:52.372
I MEAN, ANYTHING
TO GET OUT OF THE HOUSE...

12:52.372 --> 12:56.076
BETWEEN 4:00 AND 6:00 MONDAY,
WEDNESDAY, AND FRIDAY,

12:56.076 --> 12:58.809
WHEN JASON WILL BE
TUTORING MAX.

12:58.809 --> 13:01.481
OKAY, PIZZA´S ON ME.
CHIN UP!

13:01.481 --> 13:03.413
WHAT DID YOU DO?

13:03.413 --> 13:05.816
LOOK, I HAD TO ASK JASON
TO KEEP TUTORING MAX, OKAY?

13:05.816 --> 13:07.257
I HAD NO CHOICE.
NO!

13:07.257 --> 13:08.388
JASON CAN´T COME BACK HERE.

13:08.388 --> 13:10.090
ALL RIGHT.

13:10.090 --> 13:12.863
I KNOW JASON IS HELPING MAX,
BUT CARMEN IS HURTING.

13:12.863 --> 13:14.925
WHY CAN´T MAX STUDY
AT JASON´S HOUSE?

13:14.925 --> 13:18.568
WHO´S GONNA TAKE HIM?
YOU WORK, AND I WORK.

13:18.568 --> 13:21.301
WHY DO WE HAVE TO GET INVOLVED
WITH JASON AT ALL?

13:21.301 --> 13:24.534
GOD, NOBODY IN THIS HOUSE
CARES HOW I FEEL!

13:24.534 --> 13:26.837
WHERE´S SHE GOING?
WE´RE IN HER ROOM.

13:28.939 --> 13:31.912
GET OUT OF MY ROOM.

13:33.914 --> 13:37.287
LOOK, I KNOW YOU HATE ME
RIGHT NOW.

13:37.287 --> 13:40.921
OKAY, BUT I JUST WANT TO SAY
BEFORE I LEAVE...

13:40.921 --> 13:43.253
ARE YOU IN ON THIS PIZZA
OR WHAT?

13:46.326 --> 13:49.059
MOM, DAD, THIS IS
MY NEW LAB PARTNER, BRAD.

13:49.059 --> 13:51.902
HI.
NICE TO MEET YOU GUYS.

13:51.902 --> 13:53.363
IT´S KIND OF
A FUNNY STORY HOW --

13:53.363 --> 13:54.834
SHUT UP, BRAD.
OKAY.

13:56.506 --> 13:58.438
WE´RE GONNA DO HOMEWORK.

13:58.438 --> 14:02.572
OH, JUST SO YOU KNOW, MAX IS
STUDYING OUTSIDE WITH HIS TUTOR.

14:02.572 --> 14:05.876
[ CHUCKLES ] PLEASE.
I AM SO OVER THAT.

14:07.417 --> 14:09.279
SEE, ANGIE?

14:09.279 --> 14:10.981
SHE´S MOVED ON.

14:10.981 --> 14:13.583
YOU CAN TELL ME
I´M RIGHT NOW.

14:13.583 --> 14:15.986
WE BOTH LOVE THE KIDS.

14:15.986 --> 14:18.058
IT´S NOT A COMPETITION...

14:18.058 --> 14:19.990
SAID THE LOSER.

14:22.862 --> 14:25.165
WE´RE ON THE SAME TEAM...

14:25.165 --> 14:26.436
SAID THE LOSER!

14:30.140 --> 14:31.371
[ MOANS ]

14:31.371 --> 14:35.405
SAID THE GUY WITH THE PILLOW
OVER HIS HEAD.

14:35.405 --> 14:38.108
SAID THE LOSER!

14:43.213 --> 14:44.254
HI.

14:44.254 --> 14:45.515
OH, HEY.

14:45.515 --> 14:48.088
UH, YOU KNOW BRAD,
RIGHT?

14:48.088 --> 14:49.960
UH, YEAH,
YOU LOOK FAMILIAR.

14:49.960 --> 14:53.663
YEAH, I PLAY CLARINET
IN THE BAND.

14:53.663 --> 14:56.066
REMEMBER -- REMEMBER AT
HOMECOMING WHEN YOU GUYS,

14:56.066 --> 14:58.068
YOU, LIKE, RAN OFF
ONTO THE FIELD,

14:58.068 --> 15:00.030
AND YOU KNOCKED ME OVER, AND YOU
WERE, LIKE, "OH, SORRY, DUDE."

15:00.030 --> 15:01.601
AND I WAS, LIKE,
"OH, NO, IT´S COOL."

15:01.601 --> 15:03.333
AND, LIKE, IT MIGHT --
IT MIGHT --

15:03.333 --> 15:05.505
IT MIGHT HAVE LOOKED LIKE
BACK THEN THAT I WAS CRYING,

15:05.505 --> 15:07.978
BUT I WASN´T --
I JUST HAVE ALLERGIES.

15:10.310 --> 15:12.082
IT´S GOOD TO KNOW.

15:12.082 --> 15:15.145
DON´T MIND US, WE´RE JUST GONNA
DO SOME STUDYING, TOO.

15:15.145 --> 15:16.987
COME ON.

15:16.987 --> 15:19.049
OH, WHY DON´T WE START
WITH CHEMISTRY?

15:19.049 --> 15:22.692
BECAUSE YOU AND I
HAVE SUCH GREAT CHEMISTRY.

15:22.692 --> 15:24.324
Brad: OH, WELL,

15:24.324 --> 15:27.197
YOU AND I ARE BOTH COMPRISED
OF HYDROGEN AND CARBON,

15:27.197 --> 15:29.529
SO I GUESS WE DO HAVE
A LOT IN COMMON.

15:29.529 --> 15:32.102
YOU´RE SO SMART!

15:37.507 --> 15:40.610
OH, THAT´S IT.
HEY!

15:40.610 --> 15:43.373
[ Laughing ] STOP IT!
SAID THE LOSER!

15:43.373 --> 15:47.077
MOM, DAD, CARMEN´S KISSING
THE WEIRD CLARINET BOY.

15:47.077 --> 15:48.348
WHAT?

15:48.348 --> 15:49.649
SHE´S TRYING TO GET
JASON TO LEAVE.

15:49.649 --> 15:52.082
WHAT´S THE MATTER
WITH HER?

15:52.082 --> 15:54.054
WHY WOULD BRAD BEING HERE
BOTHER YOU, HUH?

15:54.054 --> 15:55.285
I´M NOT YOUR GIRLFRIEND
ANYMORE.

15:55.285 --> 15:57.557
IT BOTHERS ME
BECAUSE WE JUST BROKE UP.

15:57.557 --> 15:59.389
WHY WOULD YOU
WANT TO HURT ME?

15:59.389 --> 16:02.162
WELL, IF YOU´RE HURT,
THEN YOU SHOULD LEAVE.

16:02.162 --> 16:04.234
I THINK WHAT SHE´S TRYING TO SAY
IS THAT SHE´S WITH ME NOW.

16:04.234 --> 16:05.965
SHUT UP, HELMET HAIR.

16:07.067 --> 16:08.638
OKAY,
YOU DON´T WANT ME HERE?

16:08.638 --> 16:10.440
NO.
FINE.

16:10.440 --> 16:12.302
I´M LEAVING.
GOOD.

16:12.302 --> 16:14.174
OH, JASON, JASON,
WHERE YOU GOING?

16:14.174 --> 16:16.106
I´M SORRY, MR. LOPEZ, I´LL
HELP YOU FIND ANOTHER TUTOR,

16:16.106 --> 16:17.647
BUT I CAN´T BE HERE
RIGHT NOW.

16:19.379 --> 16:21.281
YOU RUINED IT!

16:21.281 --> 16:26.256
YOU JUST COULDN´T HANDLE
THE FACT THAT HE´S MINE NOW!

16:33.523 --> 16:35.195
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

16:35.195 --> 16:38.298
TRYING TO GET THE TASTE OF
BRAD´S TONGUE OUT OF MY MOUTH.

16:47.437 --> 16:49.279
LOOK, WE NEED TO TALK.

16:49.279 --> 16:52.082
YOU CAN BEGIN WITH THE "MAX
IS MORE IMPORTANT" SPEECH NOW.

16:52.082 --> 16:55.085
LOOK, MAX IS MORE IMPORTANT
AT THIS MOMENT, CARMEN.

16:55.085 --> 16:57.547
OKAY, AND THERE´S TIMES THAT
YOU´RE MORE IMPORTANT THAN MAX.

16:57.547 --> 16:59.719
LOOK, IT´S NOT EASY,
BUT SOMETIMES YOUR MOTHER AND I

16:59.719 --> 17:01.751
HAVE TO DO THINGS THAT AREN´T
GOOD FOR EVERYBODY.

17:01.751 --> 17:05.255
NAME ONE TIME YOU DID
SOMETHING THAT WAS GOOD
FOR ME AND BAD FOR MAX?

17:05.255 --> 17:07.257
YOU WANT TO KNOW?
OKAY, I´LL TELL YOU.

17:07.257 --> 17:09.329
CARMEN, YOUR PRIVATE SCHOOL
COSTS SO MUCH

17:09.329 --> 17:11.301
THAT MAX ISN´T GONNA
GET A NEW BIKE,

17:11.301 --> 17:14.234
HE´S NOT GETTING A COMPUTER,
AND HE´S NEVER GETTING BRACES.

17:14.234 --> 17:17.707
I DIDN´T REALIZE
HE WAS GIVING ALL THAT UP.

17:17.707 --> 17:20.410
WELL, NEITHER DOES HE,
SO DON´T SAY NOTHING.

17:26.116 --> 17:29.179
YOU DON´T UNDERSTAND.

17:29.179 --> 17:31.481
I STILL LOVE JASON.

17:31.481 --> 17:33.283
LOVE...[ SIGHS ]

17:33.283 --> 17:36.126
CARMEN, YOU´RE NOT ALLOWED
TO USE THAT WORD.

17:36.126 --> 17:37.427
CARMEN, YOU´RE 15.

17:37.427 --> 17:40.290
JULIET WAS 15,
AND SHE DIED FOR HER LOVE.

17:40.290 --> 17:42.292
WELL, THAT´S WHY WE SEND YOU
TO PRIVATE SCHOOL --

17:42.292 --> 17:43.833
TO KEEP YOU AWAY
FROM GIRLS LIKE THAT!

17:43.833 --> 17:47.397
WHY DO I EVEN BOTHER?

17:47.397 --> 17:49.469
LOOK, YOU´RE NOT GONNA
WANT TO HEAR THIS,

17:49.469 --> 17:51.771
BUT I´M GONNA
SAY IT ANYWAYS.

17:51.771 --> 17:54.073
YOU JUST HAD
A HIGH-SCHOOL BREAKUP.

17:54.073 --> 17:55.645
AND MONTHS FROM NOW,
YOU´LL FORGET ABOUT HIM,

17:55.645 --> 17:57.377
AND YOU´LL MOVE ON.

17:57.377 --> 18:00.650
BUT MAX ISN´T GONNA MOVE ON
UNLESS HE GETS HELP FROM JASON.

18:00.650 --> 18:03.513
SO JASON HAS TO COME BACK HERE
AND TUTOR HIM, OKAY,

18:03.513 --> 18:05.855
SO GO AHEAD AND YELL.

18:08.588 --> 18:11.321
NO.

18:11.321 --> 18:13.823
I´LL GO OVER TO JASON´S HOUSE
TOMORROW

18:13.823 --> 18:15.465
AND GET HIM TO COME BACK.

18:17.527 --> 18:19.269
OH, THANK YOU.

18:21.431 --> 18:26.176
SO, YOU PROMISE ME MAX WILL
NEVER GET TO WEAR BRACES?

18:27.877 --> 18:29.779
NOT AS LONG AS I´M ALIVE.

18:29.779 --> 18:31.441
[ GIGGLES ]

18:31.441 --> 18:36.746
NO BRACES, NO FILLINGS,
NO VACCINATIONS WHATSOEVER.

18:36.746 --> 18:38.548
DIDN´T HE ALREADY GET THOSE?

18:38.548 --> 18:40.820
Shh!

18:40.820 --> 18:43.293
DID I GET MY VACCINATIONS?

18:50.500 --> 18:55.165
OF COURSE YOU DID, CARMEN,
BECAUSE WE LOVE YOU.

18:59.509 --> 19:02.512
Carmen: YEE HAW!
GIDDY-UP!

19:02.512 --> 19:04.143
WHOA!

19:05.675 --> 19:07.677
[ GIGGLES ]

19:07.677 --> 19:09.179
WE´RE BACK TOGETHER.

19:09.179 --> 19:10.580
UH...

19:10.580 --> 19:14.454
I GOT SOME SUGAR CUBES
IN MY POCKET, HORSEY.

19:22.592 --> 19:26.666
I THINK HE´D RATHER BE GLUE
THERE, SEABISCUIT.

19:28.398 --> 19:31.941
I THINK I´M GONNA HELP MAX
WITH HIS HOMEWORK.

19:31.941 --> 19:33.543
SO...

19:33.543 --> 19:36.646
YOU TALKED IT OUT AND BOTH
FOUND A WAY TO COMPROMISE?

19:36.646 --> 19:39.749
NO, HE SAID HE REALLY LIKED MY
SWEATER, AND WE STARTED KISSING.

19:43.953 --> 19:45.955
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

19:45.955 --> 19:47.517
COMING.

19:49.819 --> 19:52.892
HELLO, MAX.

19:52.892 --> 19:55.595
I´M SO SORRY TO HEAR ABOUT
THE TERRIBLE ACCIDENT

19:55.595 --> 19:58.398
THAT KILLED YOUR PARENTS
AND YOUR GRANDMA.

19:58.398 --> 19:59.499
AND MY SISTER.

19:59.499 --> 20:00.970
AND YOUR SISTER.

20:04.374 --> 20:06.936
BUT...I´M HERE
TO TAKE CARE OF YOU.

20:06.936 --> 20:09.208
OF COURSE, WE´LL HAVE
TO PULL YOU OUT OF SCHOOL

20:09.208 --> 20:12.242
SO YOU´LL HAVE MORE TIME FOR
VIDEO GAMES AND SKATEBOARDING.

20:12.242 --> 20:14.614
REALLY?
YES.

20:14.614 --> 20:16.346
I´LL RAISE YOU
AS MY CHILD

20:16.346 --> 20:19.949
UNTIL YOU´RE OLD ENOUGH
TO BE...MY HUSBAND.

20:21.291 --> 20:22.922
George: MAX!

20:22.922 --> 20:25.995
I CRAWLED OUT
OF THE WRECKAGE.

20:29.999 --> 20:33.002
JUST SO I COULD
TAKE CARE OF YOU.

20:33.002 --> 20:35.865
MY SON, MAX.

20:35.865 --> 20:39.939
NOOOOOO!

20:42.011 --> 20:44.013
ANOTHER ASHLEY DREAM?

20:44.013 --> 20:45.875
YEAH.
